[at_file=file] 
[m=50]  number of sparse environments, 50-500 is useful
[r_cut=2.75] cutoff for GAP environment
[j_max=4] max of expansion of bispectrum
[z0=0.0] ???

[coordinates] {bispectrum,qw,water_monomer} representation to use (bispectrum default)

QW parameters:
[l_max=6] maximum sphearical harmonic expansion
[cutoff={:}] cutoffs for the radial basis functions, 
[cutoff_f={:}] types of the radial basis functions: 1 - Fermi, 2 - Gaussian, 3 - Skewed Gaussian
[cutoff_r1={:}] characteristic width of the cutoff function
[no_q] turn off Qs
[no_w] turn off Ws

[e0=0.0] value to be subtracted from energies before fittint (and added back on after prediction)
[f0=avg] mean of the gp predictor, defaults to data mean. another useful value is 0.0
[sgm={0.1 0.1 0.1}] error in [energies forces virials]
[dlt=1.0] ???

developer's controls: [theta_file=file] [sparse_file=file] [do_test_gp_gradient=F] [bispectrum_file=file]
[theta_fac=3.0] controls the widths of Gaussians. the range of the data is multiplied by this factor (separately for each dimension in feature space)

Optimise hyper parameters: [do_sigma=F] [do_delta=F] [do_theta=F] [do_sparx=F] [do_f0=F] [do_theta_fac=F] 

[do_cluster=F] do k-means clustering of data points to initialise the sparsifier
[do_pivot=F] initialise the sparsifier by looking at the covariance matrix
[min_steps=10] [min_save=0] paramters for hyper optimisation
[z_eff={Ga:1.0:N:-1.0}] fixed charge Coulomb interaction, subtracted from data before fitting, and added back after prediction
[ip_args={}] QUIP init string for a potential to subtract from data (and added back after prediction)
[do_ewald_corr=F] ???
[energy_property_name=energy] [force_property_name=force] [virial_property_name=virial] names of properties in the at_file that describe the data

